name: parker-river-national-wildlife-refuge-plum-island-thacher-island-national-wildlife-refuge--adeff
notes: This annual narrative report for Parker River National Wildlife Refuge and Thacher's Island National Wildlife Refuge outlines Refuge accomplishments during the 1994 calendar year. The report begins with a summary of the year's highlights and weather conditions. Land acquisition is covered. Refuge planning topics include the master plan, the management plan, public participation, compliance with environmental and cultural resource mandates, and research and investigations. Refuge administration is outlined; information about personnel, youth programs, other work problems, volunteer programs, funding, safety, and technical assistance is given. Habitat management is also covered; subjects include wetlands, grasslands, haying, fire management, pest control, and wilderness areas. The wildlife section of the report discusses wildlife diversity, endangered and threatened species, waterfowl, marsh birds and waterbirds, shorebirds, raptors, other migratory birds, game mammals, marine mammals, other resident wildlife, animal control, marking and bird banding, and disease prevention and control. The public uses of the Refuge described in this report include outdoor classrooms, interpretive programs, hunting, fishing, wildlife observation, other wildlife-oriented recreation, picnicking, off-road vehicling, other non-wildlife oriented recreation, and law enforcement. The equipment and facilities section of the report provides information about new construction, rehabilitation, equipment utilization and replacement, and computer systems. Cooperative programs and items of interest are provided at the end. Refuge brochures and field guides are attached.
